I have recently found my new home and hit me if im wrong but DAMN is it mage heaven. Its name you ask? none other than the so loved Ocean of Tears. The only downside i really see to this zone is the boat ride in, otherwise its perfect. At 46 or so you can start here killing Seafury Cyclopses on SF isle although i would recommend on starting at 49 because of the better pets the bolt (with amazing distance) and he damage shield. You dont even need sow to pull either. Make your camp at one of the corners of the isle jutting out into the ocean and have your pet guard. Put burnout on him and go pull, keep in mind tho these guys have 4200 hit points so have sufficent mana for it especially on your first few pulls. Run up the isle and bolt/dd a clops and take off towards your pet, if done right he wont even get a hit off and if he does it is weak compared to other mobs. Then have your pet attack and DS him, if you have bolt hit him 2 times and med, your pet will do the rest. These guys are idiots so they most often will stay on your pet because he is the one auctually hitting him making overnuke aggros rare and often short. This does have its dangers as well though and since its a pain to gate and wait for boat simply bind in Sisters isle gate there and camp when the battle gets too intense. These guys have an uncommon drop of cash gems and jewlry selling up to 97pp a pop. they also drop seafoam mugs and cyc toes. (note: many of the gems are for mage focus) there is also a giant there named gornit that drops all types of giant toes so if your yound and need focus items simply ask the man camping him for them =P other ofcus drops here are mermaid scales and Gargoyle eyes. This zone also gives you a rare oppurtunity at camping the ancient Cyclops (if you can wait out the list) which means you will never have to  worry about sow again if you are so commited. This place is perfect for mages and can be hunted in effectively untill lvl 53 or so. Mobs to watch out for are Quag Maelstrom (bard epic guy) who hits for 117 and mana taps. As well as tainted/corrupted Seafury. Tainted hits for 120ish and corrupted hits for 145ish and summons which means if he aggros you ARE dead. I hope this info is all helpful to you gus =) GL<br>
<br>
Deltanamos Sumnor<br>
